
# 🌟 Linux Course Recap & Command Summary

---

## 📊 Total Commands Learned
- **Approx. 150 Commands** were covered throughout this course.
- Commands range from **basic file operations** to **advanced system administration**.

---

## 🗂️ Commands A–Z Overview

### 🔹 Alias & System Info
| Command | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| **alias** | Create shortcuts for long commands. `unalias` to remove. |
| **arch** | Show system architecture (32-bit / 64-bit). |
| **at** | Schedule **one-time jobs**. Use `man at` for syntax. |

---

### 📂 File Processing & Shell Utilities
| Command | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| **awk** | Extract specific fields from output. Example: `ls -ltr | awk '{print $1}'` |
| **bash** | Check current shell → `echo $SHELL` |
| **bc** | Calculator utility. Type `bc` to enter, `Ctrl+C` to exit. |
| **cal** | Display calendar. |
| **case** | Scripting conditional option block. |
| **cat** | View file contents. |
| **cd** | Change directory. |

---

### 🔐 Password & Permissions
| Command | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| **chage** | Manage password expiry settings. |
| **chgrp** | Change group ownership. |
| **chmod** | Modify file permissions. |
| **chown** | Change file owner. |

---

### 🖥️ System & Disk Utilities
| Command | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| **clear** | Clear terminal screen. |
| **cmp** | Compare files byte-by-byte. |
| **cp** | Copy files/directories. |
| **crontab** | Schedule **repetitive jobs**. |
| **df** | Display disk space usage. Use `df -h` for human-readable format. |
| **du** | Show size of a directory. Example: `du -sh Pictures/` |

---

### 🌐 Networking & Firewall
| Command | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| **dig** | DNS lookup utility. |
| **ifconfig** | Display network interfaces. Use `ip a` on newer systems. |
| **iptables** | Legacy firewall management. |
| **firewall-cmd** | Modern firewall management tool. |
| **netstat** | Show active network connections. |
| **tcpdump** | Capture network traffic. |

---

### 👥 User Management
| Command | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| **useradd** | Create new user. |
| **usermod** | Modify user properties. |
| **userdel** | Delete a user. |
| **groupadd** | Create new group. |
| **passwd** | Change password. |

---

### 💾 File Systems & LVM
| Command | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| **mkfs** | Create a new filesystem. |
| **mount** | Mount a filesystem. |
| **umount** | Unmount a filesystem. |
| **pvcreate** | Create physical volume for LVM. |
| **vgcreate** | Create volume group for LVM. |
| **lvcreate** | Create logical volume. |
| **xfs_growfs** | Extend XFS filesystem. |

---

### 📝 Text & File Editors
| Command | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| **vi** | Text editor. |
| **nano** | Simple editor (if installed). |
| **grep** | Search text in files. |
| **less/more** | Read files page-by-page. |
| **tail** | View last 10 lines of a file. |
| **head** | View first 10 lines of a file. |

---

### ⚙️ Process Management
| Command | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| **ps** | List running processes. |
| **top** | Monitor processes in real-time. |
| **kill** | Kill process by PID. |
| **pkill** | Kill process by name. |
| **nohup** | Keep processes running after logout. |

---

## 🎯 Key Takeaways
- **~150 commands mastered**, covering:
  - File management
  - Networking
  - Security
  - Process control
  - Scripting
- Alphabetical organization makes review easy.
- **Scripting integration** for automation was a major focus.

---

## 🚀 Next Steps
- Practice these commands daily.  
- Build scripts for real-world tasks.  
- Explore **Linux server administration projects**.

> *"Mastery comes with consistent practice!"* 💪